==English==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|fr|intransigeance}}, noun form of {{m|fr|intransigeant}}, borrowed from {{der|en|es|intransigente}} at the end of the nineteenth century. Morphologically, from {{m|fr|in-}} + {{m|fr|transiger}} + {{m|fr|-ant}}, literally "[[uncompromising]]".

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ɪnˈtɹæn.sɪ.d͡ʒəns/}}
